divs: Sighting Detailswe were sitting on our back deck having a bbq, i was watching the storm clouds move in, saw a long semi circle of black dots flying from the sw to the ne at a high rate of speed. I would estimate the objects flew about 5 miles in about 20-30 seconds then we lost the in the clouds. one of the guys thought they might have been ducks, i dont think so, ducks don't fly high enough to go through clouds let alone storm clouds, and i did not see any wings, when ducks fly you can clearly see their wings. I do a lot of fishing I am very familiar with the local wildlife, I have never seen birds fly that high, was almost a perfect semi circle, and flying way too fast
trends: There have been 3 other sightings in Chester
There were no other sightings in Chester on or around May 25th 2009
Summary: 30-50 black dots high in the sky flew through storm clouds at a high rate of speed.
